  "description": "<h4>Application:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Honda CRV 1996</li>\n<li>Honda CRV 1997</li>\n<li>Honda CRV 1998</li>\n<li>Honda CRV 1999</li>\n<li>Honda CRV 2000</li>\n<li>Honda CRV 2001</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Package Includes:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>2 pieces Front coilovers</li>\n<li>2 pieces Rear coilovers</li>\n<li>2 spanners</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Features:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Mono-tube shock design provides larger capacity of oil and gas</li>\n<li>Adjustable ride height</li>\n<li>Adjustable pre-load spring tension</li>\n<li>Pillow ball top mount, this design helps combat noise while tuning and improves steering feel and response</li>\n<li>Hi Tensile performance spring, tested continuously over 600,000 times with less than 0.04% distortion; special surface treatment improves durability and performance</li>\n<li>All inserts come with fitted rubber boots to protect the damper and keep clean</li>\n<li>Improves handling performance without sacrificing comfortable ride</li>\n<li>Fast and affordable way to easily upgrade your car's appearance</li>\n<li>Easy installation with the right tools</li>\n<li>Ideal for any track, drift, fast road, and daily driving</li>\n<li>Accessories shown in photos are included</li>\n<li>Default 1-year warranty for any manufacturing defect, upgrade to 2 years with our Extended Warranty Program</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Technical Specifications:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Spring rate Front: 12 kg/mm</li>\n<li>Spring rate Rear: 6 kg/mm</li>\n<li>Adjustable height: Yes</li>\n<li>Adjustable camber plate: No</li>\n<li>Adjustable damper: Non Adjustable Damper Force</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Warranty</h4>\n<p>All items carry a standard 1-year warranty from the date of purchase. Proof of purchase is required; it is best to provide your order number. To speed up warranty claims, please send images and detailed documentation. Pictures and videos are usually sufficient; defective items usually do not need to be returned. Occasionally, more data may be requested to confirm the issue and help us provide better support.</p>",
